Stepped at PC = 0x00400004:
    memory[0x00400004] = 0x27a50004   →   addiu $a1, $sp, 4
    source line 184: 	addiu $a1 $sp 4		# argv

  Category: Arithmetic
    Integer math on registers. (COD §2.2.)
  Modifiers in `addiu`:
    `i` — immediate form: one operand is a 16-bit constant baked
          into the instruction word, not a register. Lets
          small constants be supplied without a separate
          load.
    `u` — unsigned: no trap on overflow. The plain (no-`u`) form
          traps on overflow; the `u` form silently wraps.
          Note: `u` means different things in different
          contexts — see the load modifiers.
  What it did:
    Add Immediate Unsigned — computed $sp + sign-extended immediate, no overflow trap; the result was placed in $a1.
  Inputs (before this step):
    $sp = 0x7fffffdc  (decimal 2147483612)
    immediate = 4  (0x0004)
  Wrote:
    $a1:  0x7fffffe0  →  0x7fffffe0   (decimal 2147483616)
  Try it yourself:
    print $sp
    print $a1
    print_all_regs         # show every register
  PC:  0x00400004  →  0x00400008


