  Category: Data transfer
    Move data between registers and memory.  MIPS is
    load/store — math never operates on memory directly.
    (COD §2.3, §2.9.)
  Modifiers in `lb`:
    `b` — byte width: the load/store transfers 8 bits — the smallest
          addressable unit on MIPS.  No alignment
          requirement.  Plain (no-`u`) loads sign-extend
